Defendant James A Boyd in court with attorneys Michael G. Levine and Robert Levine.  Defendant James A Boyd in custody.  Benjamin A. Wesson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Matter before the Court for Plea and Sentencing.  Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNTS 2 and 3:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting in regards to Count 2.  Filed, Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement. 

AS TO COUNT 1:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on state's motion, the Court orders Count 1 DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing in Counts 2 and 3. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense, Shirron J.-B., and defendant. 
 
AS TO COUNT 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 8 YEARS, CONCURRENT with Count 3, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 100 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4 YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 4 YEARS.

The defendant IS ELIGIBLE for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program AFTER SERVING THE FIRST 2 YEARS OF THESE SENTENCES.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Take any prescription medication only in the manner/dosage as prescribed by a treating physician;
*Cooperate with random urine screens;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with victims Tytiana D., Raidah H., Jade P., or Family Dollar stores located at 2214 N. 35th St. and 930 N. 27th St.;
*No contact with co-actor Justin Sumlin (14CF885);
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking program;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;

AS TO COUNT 3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 5 months, CONCURRENT with Count 2, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 100 days served.  

State in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution set at zero.

AS TO COUNTS 2, 3, and case 13CM004585:  Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.  Firearms and voting restrictions reiterated by the Court.  Appeal rights given.
